<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Given a processed operand Op which was promoted to a larger integer type,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// this returns the promoted value. The low bits of the promoted value</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// corresponding to the original type are exactly equal to Op.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The extra bits contain rubbish, so the promoted value may need to be zero-</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// or sign-extended from the original type before it is usable (the helpers</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// SExtPromotedInteger and ZExtPromotedInteger can do this for you).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, if Op is an i16 and was promoted to an i32, then this method</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// returns an i32, the lower 16 bits of which coincide with Op, and the upper</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 16 bits of which contain rubbish.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue">SDValue</a> GetPromotedInteger(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue">SDValue</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ab471937b9a227e70c7fe8bd9604014d6">Op</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="252"><Highlight kind="normal">    TableId &amp;PromotedId = PromotedIntegers&#91;getTableId(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ab471937b9a227e70c7fe8bd9604014d6">Op</a>)&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue">SDValue</a> PromotedOp = getSDValue(PromotedId);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="254"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(PromotedOp.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sdvalue/#a2b08aa629a6326d1a0444ee6d477c39d">getNode</a>() &amp;&amp; </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;Operand wasn&#39;t promoted?&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00255" /><CodeLine lineNumber="255"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> PromotedOp;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="441"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Given a processed operand Op which was expanded into two integers of half</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="442"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the size, this returns the two halves. The low bits of Op are exactly</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="443"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// equal to the bits of Lo; the high bits exactly equal Hi.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="444"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, if Op is an i64 which was expanded into two i32&#39;s, then this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00445" /><CodeLine lineNumber="445"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// method returns the two i32&#39;s, with Lo being equal to the lower 32 bits of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00446" /><CodeLine lineNumber="446"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Op, and Hi being equal to the upper 32 bits.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00541" /><CodeLine lineNumber="541"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// GetSoftenedFloat - Given a processed operand Op which was converted to an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00542" /><CodeLine lineNumber="542"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// integer of the same size, this returns the integer.  The integer contains</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="543"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// exactly the same bits as Op - only the type changed.  For example, if Op</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="544"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// is an f32 which was softened to an i32, then this method returns an i32,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="545"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the bits of which coincide with those of Op</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="546"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> GetSoftenedFloat(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> Op) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="547"><Highlight kind="normal">    TableId <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/amdgpu/vgprindexmode/#a9afd95476c40096a5898ba0f06370b3a">Id</a> = getTableId(Op);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="548"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-cskyconstantislandpass-cpp-/#a0bd7d621ba8de56e4052df49da823802">Iter</a> = SoftenedFloats.find(Id);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="549"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Iter == SoftenedFloats.end()) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="550"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(isSimpleLegalType(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/amdgpu/sendmsg/#a8594419a4ddfad2c9a79279c490e466d">Op</a>.getValueType()) &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="551"><Highlight kind="normal">             </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;Operand wasn&#39;t converted to integer?&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="552"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/amdgpu/sendmsg/#a8594419a4ddfad2c9a79279c490e466d">Op</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="553"><Highlight kind="normal">    &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="554"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64isellowering-cpp/#a51cb24bd3e700fcf2f93d1afbb555a16">SDValue</a> SoftenedOp = getSDValue(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-cskyconstantislandpass-cpp-/#a0bd7d621ba8de56e4052df49da823802">Iter</a>-&gt;second);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="555"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(SoftenedOp.getNode() &amp;&amp; </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;Unconverted op in SoftenedFloats?&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="556"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> SoftenedOp;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Given a processed operand Op which was expanded into two floating-point</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// values of half the size, this returns the two halves.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The low bits of Op are exactly equal to the bits of Lo; the high bits</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// exactly equal Hi.  For example, if Op is a ppcf128 which was expanded</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// into two f64&#39;s, then this method returns the two f64&#39;s, with Lo being</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// equal to the lower 64 bits of Op, and Hi to the upper 64 bits.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="904"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Given a processed vector Op which was split into vectors of half the size,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// this method returns the halves. The first elements of Op coincide with the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00906" /><CodeLine lineNumber="906"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// elements of Lo; the remaining elements of Op coincide with the elements of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00907" /><CodeLine lineNumber="907"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Hi: Op is what you would get by concatenating Lo and Hi.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00908" /><CodeLine lineNumber="908"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, if Op is a v8i32 that was split into two v4i32&#39;s, then this</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1007"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1008"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Given a processed vector Op which was widened into a larger vector, this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1009"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// method returns the larger vector. The elements of the returned vector</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1010"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// consist of the elements of Op followed by elements containing rubbish.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1011"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, if Op is a v2i32 that was widened to a v4i32, then this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1012"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// method returns a v4i32 for which the first two elements are the same as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1013"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// those of Op, while the last two elements contain rubbish.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1015"><Highlight kind="normal">    TableId &amp;WidenedId = WidenedVectors&#91;getTableId(Op)&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
